info:
  description:  |
    This entity contains a harmonised description of the environmental conditions observed at a particular location and time. This entity is primarily associated with the vertical segment of the environment and agriculture but may also be used in smart home, smart cities, industry and related IoT applications.
  title: EnvironmentObserved
  version: "0.0.1"
openapi: "3.0.0"

    get: 
      description: "Retrieve a set of entities which matches a specific query from an NGSI-LD system"
      parameters: 
        - 
          in: query
          name: type
          required: true
          schema: 
            enum: 
              - EnvironmentObserved
            type: string
      responses: 
        ? "200"
        : 
          content: 
            application/ld+json: 
              examples: 
                keyvalues: 
                  summary: "Key-Values Pairs"
                  value: 
                    - 
                      $ref: "https://smart-data-models.github.io/dataModel.Environment/EnvironmentObserved/examples/example.json"
                normalized: 
                  summary: "Normalized NGSI-LD"
                  value: 
                    - 
                      $ref: "https://smart-data-models.github.io/dataModel.Environment/EnvironmentObserved/examples/example-normalized.jsonld"
          description: OK
      tags: 
        - ngsi-ld

  - 
    description: "NGSI-LD Linked-data Format"
    name: ngsi-ld
